Package com.whirvis.jraknet

JRakNet is a networking library for Java which implements the UDP based protocol RakNet.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Packet
    A generic packet that has the ability to read and write data to and from a source buffer.
    RakNet
    The main RakNet component class, containing protocol information and utility methods.
    RakNet.BootstrapHandler
    Used by the RakNet.createBootstrapAndSend(InetSocketAddress, Packet, long, int) method to wait for a packet.
    RakNet.UPnPResult
    A Thread which runs in the background to allow for code relating to UPnP to be executed through the WaifUPnP without locking up the main thread.
    RakNetClientTest
    Tests the RakNetClient by connecting to the LifeBoat Survival Games server.
    RakNetPacket
    A generic RakNet packet that has the ability to get the ID of the packet along with encoding and decoding.
    RakNetServerTest
    Tests RakNetServer by starting a server on the default Minecraft port.
    RakNetTest
    Used to test the various functions in the RakNet class.
    SequencedPacketTest
    Tests the sequenced packet feature of the RakNetPeer through a stress test.
    SplitPacketTest
    Test the split packet feature of the RakNetPeer through a stress test.

Package com.whirvis.jraknet Description

JRakNet is a networking library for Java which implements the UDP based protocol RakNet. This library was meant to be used for Minecraft servers and clients, but can still be used to create game servers and clients for other video games with ease.
Since:
JRakNet v1.0.0
Author:
Trent Summerlin
See Also:
RakNet, RakNetServer, RakNetClient
